  "text": "The earliest gestation at which placenta accreta was encountered in our study is 8 weeks which was a caesarean scar pregnancy. There are reports of women when woman was taken up for dilatation and curettage, developed torrential hemorrhage necessitating hysterectomy and pathologic examination later revealed MAP [CITATION_1] . According to literature the earliest gestation at which placenta accreta has been diagnosed by ultrasound is 9 weeks in a case of scar pregnancy. The woman continued pregnancy and underwent emergency cesarean hysterectomy at 37 weeks because of placenta increta [CITATION_2] .",
